## Agent Planning
- Project-local guidance overrides these defaults
- Task-specific specs, plans, and scratch notes are temporary working artifacts. Store outside committed project docs (prefer `.agent/tasks/<date>-<slug>/`); do not commit unless project guidance requires it. Delete on completion; promote only durable outcomes into the project's existing documentation system. Don't add personal scratch paths to a project's `.gitignore` — covered by my global ignore.
- Promote outcomes by intent: architectural choices to ADRs (if used); current architecture to living design docs; usage/operations/schemas to reference docs; repeatable agent rules to AGENTS.md; remaining work to the issue/TODO system. Ask before creating a new convention.
- Spec authoring: surface open questions to me; never silently resolve. Before asking for spec review, list every gap-fill decision and confirm each. "Fix TBDs" means ask, not decide. Do not proceed to plan-writing with unconfirmed decisions.
- Plans: ~500 lines max; break larger plans into chunks. Insert spec review checkpoints between logical groups during execution.
- Track verification and manual steps explicitly; surface human-only blockers rather than silently skip; summarize remaining verification at completion in one message.
